#: ../../../common/conancenter_frozen.inc:3
msgid "**Default Remote Update in Conan 2.9.2**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../common/conancenter_frozen.inc:5
msgid ""
"Starting from **Conan version 2.9.2**, the default remote has been changed "
"to `https://center2.conan.io`. The previous default remote `https://center."
"conan.io` is now frozen and will no longer receive updates. It is "
"recommended to update your remote configuration to use the new default "
"remote to ensure access to the latest recipes and package updates (for more "
"information, please read this `post <https://blog.conan.io/2024/09/30/Conan-"
"Center-will-stop-receiving-updates-for-Conan-1.html>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../common/conancenter_frozen.inc:12
msgid ""
"If you still have the deprecated remote configured as the default, please "
"update using the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../common/conancenter_frozen.inc:15
msgid "conan remote update conancenter --url=\"https://center2.conan.io\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/remotes.rst:27
msgid ""
"Essentially, it tells Conan where to list/upload/download the recipes/"
"binaries from the remotes specified by their URLs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/remotes.rst:29
msgid "The fields for each remote are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/remotes.rst:31
msgid ""
"``name`` (Required, ``string`` value): Name of the remote. This name will be "
"used in commands like :ref:`reference_commands_list`, e.g., :command:`conan "
"list zlib/1.2.11 --remote my_remote_name`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/remotes.rst:33
msgid ""
"``url`` (Required, ``string`` value): indicates the URL to be used by Conan "
"to search for the recipes/binaries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/remotes.rst:34
msgid ""
"``verify_ssl`` (Required, ``bool`` value): Verify SSL certificate of the "
"specified url."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/remotes.rst:35
msgid ""
"``disabled`` (Optional, ``bool`` value, ``false`` by default): If the remote "
"is enabled or not to be used by commands like search, list, download and "
"upload. Notice that a disabled remote can be used to authenticate against it "
"even if it's disabled."
msgstr ""

